entry.def: Privet is a type of bush with small leaves that stay green all year round. It is often grown in gardens to form hedges.

means.word_mean: 1. any of various Old World shrubs having smooth entire leaves and terminal panicles of small white flowers followed by small black berries; many used for hedges
